The Foreign Secretary, who has led plans to unilaterally rewrite parts of the Northern Ireland protocol, is in the running to become the next Tory leader and Prime Minister. But officials fear if the UK goes through with the plans relations will suffer. One official told the Guardian there is a "shadow of hope" whilst the bill is out of the government's hands in the House of Lords, but added: "Campaigns generally just embed further in difficult positions and radicalise the candidates. It’s rare that you end up in a more moderate place after a bitter leadership campaign." FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES... 